p1.innerText: Artificial intelligence (AI) is intelligence demonstrated by machines, as opposed to the natural intelligence displayed by humans and animals.

p2.innerText: The term "artificial intelligence" was coined in 1956 by John McCarthy, who also organized the Dartmouth Summer Research Project on Artificial Intelligence, which is widely considered to be the birthplace of AI as a field.
